ARMs Race v0.52

Introduction
	ARMs Race is a new online game. In it, you play a sysop, starting
with a BBC micro and a single 1200 bps modem, trying to make your BBS grow.
It allows users to save games, so they can come back and play again, and
enter into competition with each other.

Installation
	ARMs Race is an ArcBBS door, number 139. It should be called like any
other door. It would be a good idea if, from the same menu, you give the
option of downloading the instructions. To get hiscores, the paramater
"-scores" should be put on the end of the line running the program.
	Once installed, ARMs Race pretty much takes care of itself. The only
thing you will need to do is watch out for later versions, which can be
collected from Northern ARM, and Arcade.
	When you collect a newer version, the file "Games" should be copied
into the new version, to keep the saved games. Most versions will be able to
handle games saved from earlier ones.

Legal Bits
	ARMs Race is shareware, in the true sense. You have a full version.
However, if you use ARMs Race on your BBS for more than two weeks, you should
send £5 to:
